Package: rodin-headless
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: headless toolchain to build, model-check, and prove Rodin Event-B models
 rodin-headless drives the Rodin Platform from the command line to build,
 model-check, and prove Event-B models without a graphical session. It takes
 the .zip archives of Event-B projects, runs a full Rodin workspace build in
 headless mode, and writes the static-checked artifacts back into the archives.
 Beyond plain builds it can model-check and validate models with ProB and
 automatically discharge proof obligations with Rodin.
 .
 It bundles no Rodin, ProB, or Java. Run "rodin-headless-install" once to fetch
 the Rodin and ProB runtimes into your per-user data directory (native mode,
 which needs a JDK 21+, Xvfb, GTK 3 and zip/unzip), or point the wrapper at a
 Docker/Podman container image. Run "rodin-headless-install --check-deps" to
 report anything that is missing.
